{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Unfortunately, the vast number of parameters in LLMs compared to traditional recommender systems results in prohibitive communication costs and impractical computational resource requirements for clients.",
    "Zhang et al. [61] proposed FedPA, which uses pretrained LLMs to provide textual item embeddings for collaborative filtering-based recommendation tasks.",
    "In contrast to FedPA, our FELLAS has at least two major differences, making them uncomparable: (1) FELLAS not only uses LLMs to provide textual item embeddings but also explores using LLMs to encode user interaction sequences.",
    "This exploration is non-trivial as FedSeqRec does not allow users to expose their original data.",
    "Thus, FELLAS implements a privacy-preserving sequence-sharing method and a contrastive learning method to learn from noisy sequence representations."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Zhang et al. [61] proposed FedPA, which uses pretrained LLMs to provide textual item embeddings for collaborative filtering-based recommendation tasks."
  ]
}